Sentencas: Electrode architecturing for fast electrochemical reaction is essential for achieving high-performance of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Vapor-Mediated Infiltration of Nanocatalysts for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Electrosprayed Dendrites

Sentencas: However, the conventional droplet infiltration technique still has limitations in terms of the applicability and scalability of nanocatalyst implementation.
Titulo: Vapor-Mediated Infiltration of Nanocatalysts for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Electrosprayed Dendrites

Sentencas: Here, we develop a novel two-step precursor infiltration process and fabricate high-performance LT-SOFCs with homogeneous and robust nanocatalysts.
Titulo: Vapor-Mediated Infiltration of Nanocatalysts for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Electrosprayed Dendrites

Sentencas: This novel infiltration process is designed based on the principle of a reversible sol-gel transition where the gelated precursor dendrites are uniformly deposited onto the electrode via controlled nanoscale electro-spraying process then resolubilized and infiltrated into the porous electrode structure through subsequent humidity control.
Titulo: Vapor-Mediated Infiltration of Nanocatalysts for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Electrosprayed Dendrites

Sentencas: Our infiltration technique reduces the cathodic polarization resistance by 18% compared to conventional processes, thereby achieving an enhanced peak power density of 0.976 W cm(-2) at 650 degrees C. These results, which provide various degrees of freedom for forming nanocatalysts, exhibit an advancement in LT-SOFC technology.
Titulo: Vapor-Mediated Infiltration of Nanocatalysts for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using Electrosprayed Dendrites
